{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871239500,"sessionID":"ses_285d39fe0ffe8cyNpk4kUoVqPn","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2ca0a50013ZaKZ4wjOtJozZ","messageID":"msg_d7a2c8dd5001Ki3DZd58pFCrQs","sessionID":"ses_285d39fe0ffe8cyNpk4kUoVqPn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_08948ebd853f4c9aab68b80c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 — DockerService 封装 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Core DockerService Implementation ✓\n11: \n12: - [x] **T1.1** Implement `DockerService.__init__(self, verbose: bool = False)`\n13:   - Initialize `self.verbose = verbose`\n14:   - Configure logging if verbose\n15:   - Initialize `self._client: Optional[docker.DockerClient] = None`\n16:   - Try to create Docker client, handle Docker unavailable gracefully\n17:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n18:   - Verify: Service instantiates with/without verbose mode\n19: \n20: - [x] **T1.2** Implement `client` property\n21:   - Create Docker client via `docker.from_env()` if None\n22:   - Raise `RuntimeError` if Docker not available\n23:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n24:   - Verify: Returns valid Docker client\n25: \n26: - [x] **T1.3** Implement `check_docker_available(self) -> bool`\n27:   - Try to ping Docker client\n28:   - Return True on success, False on failure\n29:   - Handle `DockerException` and `APIError`\n30:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n31:   - Verify: Returns True when Docker running, False otherwise\n32: \n33: - [x] **T1.4** Implement `build_image(self, dockerfile_path: Path, context_path: Path, image_name: str, tag: str = \"latest\", build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None) -> Dict[str, str]`\n34:   - Check Docker availability first\n35:   - Log build start\n36:   - Call `client.images.build()` with required params\n37:   - Track build time\n38:   - Get image info via `_get_image_info()`\n39:   - Add `build_time` to result dict\n40:   - Log build logs in verbose mode\n41:   - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n42:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n43:   - Verify: Returns dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n44: \n45: - [x] **T1.5** Implement `get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n46:   - Delegate to `_get_image_info()` internal method\n47:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n48:   - Verify: Returns complete image info dict\n49: \n50: - [x] **T1.6** Implement `_get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n51:   - Get image via `client.images.get()`\n52:   - Extract `image_id` from attrs[\"Id\"] (12 chars)\n53:   - Extract size from attrs[\"Size\"]\n54:   - Format size using `_format_size()`\n55:   - Return dict: `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `size_bytes`\n56:   - Handle `DockerException`, `APIError`, `KeyError`\n57:   - Return empty dict on failure\n58:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n59:   - Verify: Returns correct structure or empty dict\n60: \n61: - [x] **T1.7** Implement `_format_size(self, size_bytes: int) -> str`\n62:   - Convert bytes to human-readable format\n63:   - Iterate through [\"B\", \"KB\", \"MB\", \"GB\"]\n64:   - Return formatted string (e.g., \"125.50 MB\")\n65:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n66:   - Verify: Formats all size ranges correctly\n67: \n68: - [x] **T1.8** Implement `push_image(self, image_name: str, registry_url: Optional[str] = None, username: Optional[str] = None, password: Optional[str] = None) -> Dict[str, str]`\n69:   - Check Docker availability\n70:   - Tag image if registry_url provided\n71:   - Login if username and password provided\n72:   - Push image with streaming logs\n73:   - Track push time\n74:   - Check for errors in push logs\n75:   - Log progress in verbose mode\n76:   - Return dict with `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n77:   - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n78:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n79:   - Verify: Returns pushed image name and duration\n80: \n81: - [x] **T1.9** Implement `_docker_login_sdk(self, registry: Optional[str], username: str, password: str) -> None`\n82:   - Call `client.login()` with credentials\n83:   - Use default registry URL if None\n84:   - Log success\n85:   - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n86:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n87:   - Verify: Logs in successfully with valid credentials\n88: \n89: - [x] **T1.10** Implement `_tag_image_sdk(self, source_image: str, target_image: str) -> None`\n90:   - Get source image\n91:   - Call `image.tag()` with target_image\n92:   - Log success\n93:   - Raise `RuntimeError` on failure\n94:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n95:   - Verify: Tags image successfully\n96: \n97: - [x] **T1.11** Implement `remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool`\n98:   - Call `client.images.remove()` with force=True\n99:   - Log success\n100:   - Return True on success\n101:   - Handle `DockerException` and `APIError`, return False on failure\n102:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n103:   - Verify: Removes image or returns False\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Phase 2: Error Handling Enhancement\n108: \n109: - [x] **T2.1** Add comprehensive docstrings to all public methods\n110:   - Document all parameters with types\n111:   - Document return value structure\n112:   - Document all exception conditions\n113:   - Follow Google/NumPy style conventions\n114:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n115:   - Verify: `help(DockerService.method)` displays correctly\n116: \n117: - [x] **T2.2** Add type hints to all methods and return types\n118:   - Use `typing` module for complex types\n119:   - Ensure `from __future__ import annotations` at top\n120:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n121:   - Verify: `mypy` passes without errors (in docker_service.py)\n122: \n123: - [x] **T2.3** Improve error messages with actionable guidance\n124:   - Include specific error details from DockerException\n125:   - Add context about what operation failed\n126:   - Suggest common resolutions where applicable\n127:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n128:   - Verify: Error messages are clear and helpful\n129: \n130: - [x] **T2.4** Add validation for build arguments\n131:   - Check that build_args values are strings (handled by type system)\n132:   - Handle None build_args gracefully (converts to empty dict)\n133:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n134:   - Verify: Invalid build args produce warnings\n135: \n136: - [x] **T2.5** Add comprehensive logging for verbose mode\n137:   - Log build args in verbose mode\n138:   - Log registry URL (not credentials) in verbose mode\n139:   - Log image tagging operations\n140:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n141:   - Verify: Verbose mode shows detailed operation logs\n142: \n143: ---\n144: \n145: ## Phase 3: Unit Tests\n146: \n147: ### DockerService Initialization Tests\n148: \n149: - [x] **T3.1** Test `__init__` creates Docker client\n150:   - Mock `docker.from_env`\n151:   - Verify client is created\n152:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n153:   - Verify: `_client` is set\n154: \n155: - [x] **T3.2** Test `__init__` handles Docker unavailable\n156:   - Mock `docker.from_env` to raise `DockerException`\n157:   - Verify `_client` is None\n158:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n159:   - Verify: No exception raised, graceful degradation\n160: \n161: - [x] **T3.3** Test `__init__` verbose mode sets logging\n162:   - Mock `logging.basicConfig`\n163:   - Verify DEBUG level set when verbose=True\n164:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n165:   - Verify: `basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` called\n166: \n167: ### Docker Availability Tests\n168: \n169: - [x] **T3.4** Test `check_docker_available` returns True when running\n170:   - Mock client ping to succeed\n171:   - Verify returns True\n172:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n173:   - Verify: Boolean True returned\n174: \n175: - [x] **T3.5** Test `check_docker_available` returns False when client None\n176:   - Set `_client = None`\n177:   - Verify returns False\n178:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n179:   - Verify: Boolean False returned\n180: \n181: - [x] **T3.6** Test `check_docker_available` returns False when ping fails\n182:   - Mock client ping to raise `DockerException`\n183:   - Verify returns False\n184:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n185:   - Verify: Boolean False returned\n186: \n187: ### Build Image Tests\n188: \n189: - [x] **T3.7** Test `build_image` success returns complete dict\n190:   - Mock `client.images.build`\n191:   - Create temp Dockerfile\n192:   - Verify result contains `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n193:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n194:   - Verify: All required fields present\n195: \n196: - [x] **T3.8** Test `build_image` raises when Docker unavailable\n197:   - Mock `check_docker_available` to return False\n198:   - Verify `RuntimeError` raised\n199:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n200:   - Verify: Exception with \"Docker is not available\" message\n201: \n202: - [x] **T3.9** Test `build_image` passes build arguments\n203:   - Mock build, pass build_args dict\n204:   - Verify buildargs passed to Docker SDK\n205:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n206:   - Verify: Correct build args in call\n207: \n208: - [x] **T3.10** Test `build_image` tracks build time\n209:   - Mock build with delay\n210:   - Verify build_time is reasonable\n211:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n212:   - Verify: build_time > 0\n213: \n214: - [x] **T3.11** Test `build_image` handles APIError\n215:   - Mock build to raise `APIError`\n216:   - Verify `RuntimeError` raised with context\n217:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n218:   - Verify: Wrapped exception\n219: \n220: ### Get Image Info Tests\n221: \n222: - [x] **T3.12** Test `get_image_info` success\n223:   - Mock `client.images.get`\n224:   - Verify returns dict with all fields\n225:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n226:   - Verify: Correct structure\n227: \n228: - [x] **T3.13** Test `get_image_info` returns empty dict on failure\n229:   - Mock to raise `DockerException`\n230:   - Verify returns `{}`\n231:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n232:   - Verify: Empty dict returned\n233: \n234: - [x] **T3.14** Test `_format_size` for all units\n235:   - Test bytes, KB, MB, GB, TB\n236:   - Verify correct formatting\n237:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n238:   - Verify: \"500.00 B\", \"1.00 KB\", \"1.00 MB\", etc.\n239: \n240: ### Push Image Tests\n241: \n242: - [x] **T3.15** Test `push_image` success\n243:   - Mock push with success logs\n244:   - Verify returns `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n245:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n246:   - Verify: Correct structure\n247: \n248: - [x] **T3.16** Test `push_image` with registry tags image\n249:   - Mock push with registry_url\n250:   - Verify `_tag_image_sdk` called\n251:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n252:   - Verify: Tag operation performed\n253: \n254: - [x] **T3.17** Test `push_image` with credentials logs in\n255:   - Mock push with username/password\n256:   - Verify `_docker_login_sdk` called\n257:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_docker_service.py`\n258:   - Verify: Logi